00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:15,230
But before that, let's understand what is Entity Framework core migrations.

4
00:00:15,770 --> 00:00:22,220
Entity framework core migrations are a powerful feature for managing database schema changes in an application's

5
00:00:22,220 --> 00:00:23,120
life cycle.

6
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:30,440
They enable a developer to evolve a database schema in a controlled and consistent way, in line with

7
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:31,190
the domain model.

8
00:00:31,190 --> 00:00:33,800
Changes in real world projects.

9
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,450
Data models change.

10
00:00:35,450 --> 00:00:42,680
As features get implemented, new entities or properties are added and removed, and database schemas

11
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:47,510
need to be changed accordingly to be kept in sync with the application.

12
00:00:48,170 --> 00:00:54,740
Migrations provide a way to incrementally update the database schema so that it stays in synchronous

13
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:56,780
with the application's data model.

14
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:03,830
It is especially useful in team environment and continuous deployment scenarios, where database schema

15
00:01:03,830 --> 00:01:07,490
changes are frequent and need to be applied systematically.

16
00:01:08,390 --> 00:01:15,860
So how Entity Framework core migration works when a data model change occurs, developers use Entity

17
00:01:15,860 --> 00:01:21,740
Framework core Tools in order to create a corresponding migration folder that describes the necessary

18
00:01:21,740 --> 00:01:22,970
database updates.

19
00:01:23,330 --> 00:01:29,240
Entity Framework Core compares the current model against a snapshot of the previous model in order to

20
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:32,510
find differences and generate migration source files.

21
00:01:32,540 --> 00:01:38,870
Once any migration has been generated, it can be applied to a database in various ways.

22
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:45,590
Entity framework Core records all applied migrations in a special history table, allowing it to know

23
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:48,890
which migrations has been applied and which haven't.

